rComments: Technical elective (selected topics) Aqueous Eng  This is her field of research so she's really into the material, but this mean she gives you much more information than you need to know. Her assignments and midterm are a little too long. But, she's really nice and lenient to her class and very personable. In my top 3 chem eng profs.

A very easy-going professor. She is always happy to answer your questions. The content of the course "Aqueous Engineering"is interesting and practical. Omelon doesn't follow the schedule, always, but it doesn't matter. Lots of assignments and reports (outline, extend outline, draft), marked seriously. Exams are not difficult but numerous questions.

Dr. Omelon has a very nice personality. She has a good attitude. She is funny and caring as well. The only thing I would add is that she is hard to follow at times, but nothing that can't be overcome with the textbook.
Really just spends the whole class writing meaningless equations on the board. Midterm was brutal but the final was very fair. Also very good looking,

Very good lecturer. Teaches the concepts and explains the theory behind the equations unlike some professors. Does example problems on the blackboard to supplement lecture slides. Always attend her lectures, since most of the material is not posted on the online slides. Most importantly, Dr. Omelon ties the material learnt in class to industry.

Absolutely hated this professor. Having two courses with her was the greatest mistake of my entire life. Boring lecture in general, and didn't follow the syllabus well (all she has done in the first three weeks is to review a prerequisite course since it was all related) If you have the chance to avoid her or neglect her, DO IT AT ALL COST.
Solid professor, and great when it comes to giving help outside the classroom.

She's not that bad of a professor as I thought she would  be compared to the earlier comments. In class, she did very descriptive derivations. She's a tough marker, she wants you to show all your work, significant figures and etc. Her assignments, midterm was fair and closely related. Her final this year was pretty hard though and it had surprises.

The comments towards professor seem harsh. Her teaching can get boring (ie: very long derivations not much explanation- but hey its thermo!) the assignments and tests were very fair and reflected what was learned in the course very closely. She focuses largely on practical explanations related to industry which gives context to the material.

Horrible! she is a total snob! thinks she knows everything and everyone else in the class is an idiot! she has no experience and has no idea what she is talking about in the class... she doesn't even know the very basics of chemical engineering or at least is not able to explain them!
Horrible slides, horrible teacher. We got stuck with her.
Hard working. Likes to teach life skills not just dry engineering equations. Great prof overall.
HORRIBLE

She's a bad prof on so many levels it beggars belief. Not clear at all in her explanations..You never really see the point of what she is trying to explain..And when you get to the quizzes, surprise; this was never covered in class!Honestly if you have her, it's nearly better not to come to class,as she will confuse you. Stick to the book and pray.

It's MANDATORY that you do EVERYTHING in your power to make sure your are NOT in her classes. Taught a French class, and failed! Should not teach period. Don't take these comments lightly! she's awful! rate her a 'minus' 10! Remember : STAY AWAY!

Do not take these comments lightly. Stay away from this teacher at all cost. She tries to teach in French, and she FAILS at it. She is a horrible teacher. We are not a few complaining students. I challenge you to find ONE student that likes this teacher. She has no business in a university class. 'Minus'!<-- inside joke with class
Very good prof "minus" everything. STAY AWAY AND GO IN THE ENGLISH SECTION AT ALL COST.
Switch out. Change programs. Do what you can but get out of there. At all cost.
Sidney is totally hot!

Where to start?               Terrible teaching style, boring and useless slides, incomprehensible presentation. Loves to show her midriff, is completely disorganized, goes through the material as if seeing it for the first time and struggles to explain, very tedious to attend lectures
